# Audio pipeline architecture

Calliop processes voice dictation through a linear pipeline orchestrated in `pipeline/`.

## Flow

```
Hotkey (toggle ON / push-to-talk hold)
  -> AudioCapture (PCM 16 kHz mono, streaming chunks)
  -> VadSegmenter (Silero VAD, filters silence)
  -> WhisperEngine (persistent context, segment transcription)
  -> partial-transcript events -> Overlay
Hotkey OFF / release (toggle or PTT)
  -> flush VAD tail + concat segments
  -> TextInjector (inject/)
  -> latency-metrics event
```

## Module responsibilities

| Module | Path | Role |
|-----|---|---|
| hotkey | `hotkey/` | Global shortcut (Alt+Espace hybrid toggle/PTT) |
| audio | `audio/` | Micro capture via cpal, VAD segmentation |
| stt | `stt/` | Local transcription (whisper.cpp / whisper-rs) |
| llm | `llm/` | Post-processing auto-edits (llama.cpp, Phase 3+) |
| inject | `inject/` | Paste/type into foreground app (enigo + clipboard fallback) |
| store | `store/` | SQLite: config, dictionary, snippets, history |
| pipeline | `pipeline/` | Orchestration, state machine, IPC bridge to frontend |

## IPC (Tauri commands)

- Frontend (React) handles overlay, settings, onboarding — no heavy ML in the webview.
- Rust core exposes commands for start/stop dictation, settings read/write, history queries.
- Events: `pipeline-state`, `partial-transcript`, `audio-level`, `latency-metrics`.

## Inference backend

- CPU is the default path (16 GB RAM target, no dedicated GPU required).
- Optional CUDA/Vulkan on Windows when available — never block on GPU.

## Phase scope

- Phase 1: hotkey -> audio -> stt -> inject (no LLM, no VAD)
- Phase 2: Silero VAD, streaming by segments, overlay, tray menu, autostart, latency debug
- STT: **whisper-rs 0.16**, persistent `WhisperEngine`, modèle `ggml-small.bin`, langue `fr`
- Audio capture runs on a dedicated thread (`cpal` streams are !Send)
- Phase 3: LLM, dictionary, snippets, app context
